The baby was caught in the crossfire of an apparent gang shooting in Windmill Park last week. JOHANNESBURG – The family of 11-month-old Siyabonga Buthelezi has had to postpone his burial for another day due to challenges with his post-mortem results. The baby was caught in the crossfire of an apparent gang shooting in Windmill Park last week. He died in hospital a day later. The family has been struggling to collect funds to bury the little boy. At the same time, the police's Mathapelo Peters said a suspect had been arrested for the shooting. “The suspect was traced by police and arrested at Tambo Memorial Hospital on Saturday, 4 January 2020. The suspect remains in custody and is due to make an appearance in court for bail application.”